{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015guebxcpHhYbWYzaWhzX43","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Backend Migration System Exploration\n\nI've thoroughly explored the backend migration system in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Migration Files Overview\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/`\n\n**Current migrations** (9 files, numbered sequentially):\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Tables/Changes |\n|------|---------|-------------------|\n| `001_init.sql` | Initial schema | `rounds` (commit-reveal game data), `operator_events` (audit log) |\n| `002_auth_sessions.sql` | JWT auth | `auth_challenges`, `refresh_tokens` |\n| `003_tier_to_amount.sql` | Remove tier model | Drops `tier` column, adds `amount_lamports` BIGINT |\n| `004_match_id_index.sql` | Query optimization | Index on `rounds(match_id)` for `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` |\n| `005_closecall_rounds.sql` | Close Call game | `closecall_rounds` table (pari-mutuel, oracle-resolved) with green/red pools |\n| `006_closecall_candles.sql` | Price history | `closecall_candles` (minute-boundary Pyth prices, VAA blobs) |\n| `007_round_entries.sql` | Player tracking | Adds `entries JSONB` column to `rounds` for settlement time data |\n| `008_user_transactions.sql` | Event logging | `user_transactions` (join/win/loss/refund events) — **deprecated, replaced by 009** |\n| `009_transactions.sql` | Transaction ledger | Drops `user_transactions`, creates `transactions` (deposit/payout/refund with tx_sig) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Migration Runner (`migrate.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n\n**Architecture**:\n- **Language**: TypeScript (ESM, runs via `tsx`)\n- **DB library**: `postgres` (node-postgres v3.4.0)\n- **Tracking**: `_migrations` table (version INT, name TEXT, applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ)\n- **Idempotency**: Each migration is idempotent; `CREATE ... IF NOT EXISTS` ensures safety\n- **Atomicity**: Each migration runs inside a `sql.begin()` transaction — partial application is impossible\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `loadMigrationFiles()` — reads numbered `.sql` files from `migrations/` dir, validates format\n- `ensureMigrationsTable()` — creates `_migrations` tracking table if missing\n- `ensureSchema()` — handles optional custom schema (`DB_SCHEMA` env var)\n- `getAppliedVersions()` — queries which migrations have been applied\n- `applyMigration()` — runs SQL + records version in one transaction\n- `runMigrations()` — applies pending migrations in order\n- `showStatus()` — CLI command to list [applied]/[pending] status\n\n**CLI Usage** (from `package.json` scripts):\n```bash\npnpm migrate              # Run pending migrations (reads DATABASE_URL env)\npnpm migrate:status      # Show migration status\nnpm run start            # Runs: migrate first, then starts server\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Database Configuration (`db-config.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n\n**Purpose**: Handle optional custom PostgreSQL schema routing\n\n**Functions**:\n- `loadDbSchemaFromEnv(env)` — reads `DB_SCHEMA` env var (defaults to `\"public\"`)\n- `applyDbSchemaToUrl(databaseUrl, schema)` — appends `-csearch_path=<schema>` to PostgreSQL connection string if schema ≠ `\"public\"`\n\n**Example**:\n```typescript\n// Input: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...\n// Output: postgresql://...?options=-csearch_path=custom_schema\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. DB Client Module (`db.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Exports**: `createDb(databaseUrl)` → `Db` interface\n\n**Db Interface Methods** (organized by entity):\n\n**Rounds** (commit-reveal):\n- `insertRound(params)` — create with phase, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, entries\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates)` — enforces state machine (created→locked→settling→settled)\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)`, `getRoundByMatchId(matchId)`\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` — for settlement workers\n- `updateRoundEntries(pda, entries)` — store winner/payout data at settlement\n- `deleteRoundByPda(pda)` — cleanup\n- `getRecentSettledRounds(game, limit)`, `getUnsettledStats()` — analytics\n\n**Operator Events** (audit log):\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload)` — log state changes (secret_generated, settle_submitted, etc.)\n- `getLatestOperatorEvent(pda, eventType)` — fetch last event of type\n- `getLatestOperatorEventsForPdas(pdas, eventType)` — batch lookup\n\n**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n- `insertCloseCallRound(params)` — create with round_id, pda, open_price\n- `getCloseCallRound(roundId)`, `getCloseCallCurrentRound()`\n- `getCloseCallHistory(limit)` — recent settled/refunded rounds\n- `settleCloseCallRound(roundId, updates)` — set phase, outcome, close_price, pools, entries\n\n**Transactions**:\n- `insertTransaction(params)`, `insertTransactions(params[])` — idempotent (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING)\n- `getTransactions(wallet, cursor?, limit?, game?)` — paginated history, newest first\n- `close()` — gracefully end connection pool\n\n**Data Normalization**:\n- All BIGINT columns (amounts, prices) are normalized to JavaScript `Number`\n- JSONB arrays parsed automatically by postgres.js\n- Date fields converted to ISO strings on insert\n\n---\n\n## 5. Auth DB Module (`auth-db.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/auth-db.ts`\n\n**Exports**: `createAuthDb(sql)` → `AuthDb` interface (shares postgres connection pool)\n\n**AuthDb Methods**:\n- `insertChallenge(nonce, wallet, cluster, message, expiresAt)` — create challenge for wallet sign-in\n- `consumeChallenge(nonce)` — atomically set used=TRUE (prevents replay)\n- `insertRefreshToken(wallet, tokenHash, familyId, expiresAt)` — store token for JWT refresh\n- `getRefreshTokenByHash(tokenHash)` — lookup by token hash\n- `revokeRefreshToken(id)` — invalidate single token\n- `revokeTokenFamily(familyId)` — detect token theft (revoke all in family)\n- `cleanupExpired()` — delete stale challenges and revoked tokens\n\n**Auth Tables**:\n- `auth_challenges` — single-use nonces for challenge-response flow\n- `refresh_tokens` — family-based revocation for JWT token rotation\n\n---\n\n## 6. Integration in `index.ts`\n\n**How migrations are invoked**:\n\n```typescript\n// From package.json \"start\" script:\n//   \"start\": \"tsx src/migrate.ts && tsx src/index.ts\"\n\n// Manual in index.ts would be:\nimport { runMigrations } from \"./migrate.js\";\nawait runMigrations(config.databaseUrl);\n```\n\n**Current setup** (index.ts lines 1–30):\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);       // Wraps postgres connection\nconst authDb = createAuthDb(sql);              // Reuses same connection pool\n\n// db and authDb share the postgres connection\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Schema Summary\n\n**Current Tables** (after all 9 migrations):\n\n| Table | Purpose | Key Columns |\n|-------|---------|------------|\n| `rounds` | Commit-reveal games (Coinflip, Lord) | pda, game, creator, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, match_id, phase (state machine), entries (JSONB), result_hash, winner |\n| `operator_events` | Audit log | pda, event_type, payload (JSONB), created_at |\n| `closecall_rounds` | Pari-mutuel prediction (BTC oracle) | round_id, pda, phase, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, green_entries (JSONB), red_entries (JSONB), close_price, settle_tx |\n| `closecall_candles` | Pyth price history | minute_ts (PK), price, expo, price_human, hermes_vaa |\n| `transactions` | Player transaction ledger | wallet, game, match_id, tx_type (deposit/payout/refund), amount_lamports, tx_sig (unique), created_at |\n| `auth_challenges` | Challenge-response nonces | nonce (PK), wallet, cluster, message, expires_at, used |\n| `refresh_tokens` | JWT token family | id, wallet, token_hash (UNIQUE), family_id, expires_at, revoked |\n| `_migrations` | Version tracking | version (PK), name, applied_at |\n\n**Indexes** (for query optimization):\n- `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `rounds(match_id)`\n- `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n- `closecall_rounds(phase)`, `closecall_rounds(settled_at DESC)`\n- `transactions(wallet, created_at DESC)`, `transactions(match_id)`\n- Unique constraints on `transactions(wallet, match_id, tx_type, tx_sig)` (idempotency guard)\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Numbered file format** (`001_`, `002_`, etc.) — lexicographic ordering ensures correct application sequence\n2. **Transactional safety** — each migration + version record in one transaction prevents partial state\n3. **Idempotent SQL** — `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` allows re-running without errors\n4. **Schema routing** — optional `DB_SCHEMA` env var for multi-tenant setups\n5. **Dev-phase destructive migrations** — `003_tier_to_amount.sql` truncates `rounds` table (acceptable during development, not production)\n6. **State machine enforcement** — phase transitions validated at application layer + recorded via `updated_at` timestamps\n7. **Audit log via operator_events** — immutable append-only record of all state changes (complementary to transaction ledger)\n8. **Idempotent transaction writes** — `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `transactions(wallet, match_id, tx_type, tx_sig)` prevents duplicate logging\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/` — all .sql files\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — migration runner\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts` — schema routing\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` — main DB client\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/auth-db.ts` — auth operations\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts` — server bootstrap\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/package.json` — npm scripts (migrate, start)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a35432f44d9c31667 (use SendMessage with to: 'a35432f44d9c31667' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 53397\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 82482</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04709d28-c77b-4687-bdb5-b2ffc1a1c744","uuid":"eabe9cdc-e702-4705-9fe7-d025d1ea8257","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:03:54.798Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the backend migration system in sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/. I need to understand:\n1. What existing migration files look like (list files in migrations/ dir, read one or two)\n2. How migrations are run (look at package.json scripts for \"migrate\")\n3. The DB client setup (find the postgres/sql import)\n4. Any migration runner code\n\nBe thorough - read actual migration files and the migration runner if one exists.","agentId":"a35432f44d9c31667","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Backend Migration System Exploration\n\nI've thoroughly explored the backend migration system in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Migration Files Overview\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/`\n\n**Current migrations** (9 files, numbered sequentially):\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Tables/Changes |\n|------|---------|-------------------|\n| `001_init.sql` | Initial schema | `rounds` (commit-reveal game data), `operator_events` (audit log) |\n| `002_auth_sessions.sql` | JWT auth | `auth_challenges`, `refresh_tokens` |\n| `003_tier_to_amount.sql` | Remove tier model | Drops `tier` column, adds `amount_lamports` BIGINT |\n| `004_match_id_index.sql` | Query optimization | Index on `rounds(match_id)` for `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` |\n| `005_closecall_rounds.sql` | Close Call game | `closecall_rounds` table (pari-mutuel, oracle-resolved) with green/red pools |\n| `006_closecall_candles.sql` | Price history | `closecall_candles` (minute-boundary Pyth prices, VAA blobs) |\n| `007_round_entries.sql` | Player tracking | Adds `entries JSONB` column to `rounds` for settlement time data |\n| `008_user_transactions.sql` | Event logging | `user_transactions` (join/win/loss/refund events) — **deprecated, replaced by 009** |\n| `009_transactions.sql` | Transaction ledger | Drops `user_transactions`, creates `transactions` (deposit/payout/refund with tx_sig) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Migration Runner (`migrate.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts`\n\n**Architecture**:\n- **Language**: TypeScript (ESM, runs via `tsx`)\n- **DB library**: `postgres` (node-postgres v3.4.0)\n- **Tracking**: `_migrations` table (version INT, name TEXT, applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ)\n- **Idempotency**: Each migration is idempotent; `CREATE ... IF NOT EXISTS` ensures safety\n- **Atomicity**: Each migration runs inside a `sql.begin()` transaction — partial application is impossible\n\n**Key Functions**:\n- `loadMigrationFiles()` — reads numbered `.sql` files from `migrations/` dir, validates format\n- `ensureMigrationsTable()` — creates `_migrations` tracking table if missing\n- `ensureSchema()` — handles optional custom schema (`DB_SCHEMA` env var)\n- `getAppliedVersions()` — queries which migrations have been applied\n- `applyMigration()` — runs SQL + records version in one transaction\n- `runMigrations()` — applies pending migrations in order\n- `showStatus()` — CLI command to list [applied]/[pending] status\n\n**CLI Usage** (from `package.json` scripts):\n```bash\npnpm migrate              # Run pending migrations (reads DATABASE_URL env)\npnpm migrate:status      # Show migration status\nnpm run start            # Runs: migrate first, then starts server\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Database Configuration (`db-config.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n\n**Purpose**: Handle optional custom PostgreSQL schema routing\n\n**Functions**:\n- `loadDbSchemaFromEnv(env)` — reads `DB_SCHEMA` env var (defaults to `\"public\"`)\n- `applyDbSchemaToUrl(databaseUrl, schema)` — appends `-csearch_path=<schema>` to PostgreSQL connection string if schema ≠ `\"public\"`\n\n**Example**:\n```typescript\n// Input: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...\n// Output: postgresql://...?options=-csearch_path=custom_schema\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. DB Client Module (`db.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n**Exports**: `createDb(databaseUrl)` → `Db` interface\n\n**Db Interface Methods** (organized by entity):\n\n**Rounds** (commit-reveal):\n- `insertRound(params)` — create with phase, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, entries\n- `updateRoundPhase(pda, newPhase, updates)` — enforces state machine (created→locked→settling→settled)\n- `getRoundByPda(pda)`, `getRoundByMatchId(matchId)`\n- `getRoundsByPhase(phase)` — for settlement workers\n- `updateRoundEntries(pda, entries)` — store winner/payout data at settlement\n- `deleteRoundByPda(pda)` — cleanup\n- `getRecentSettledRounds(game, limit)`, `getUnsettledStats()` — analytics\n\n**Operator Events** (audit log):\n- `insertOperatorEvent(pda, eventType, payload)` — log state changes (secret_generated, settle_submitted, etc.)\n- `getLatestOperatorEvent(pda, eventType)` — fetch last event of type\n- `getLatestOperatorEventsForPdas(pdas, eventType)` — batch lookup\n\n**Close Call** (pari-mutuel):\n- `insertCloseCallRound(params)` — create with round_id, pda, open_price\n- `getCloseCallRound(roundId)`, `getCloseCallCurrentRound()`\n- `getCloseCallHistory(limit)` — recent settled/refunded rounds\n- `settleCloseCallRound(roundId, updates)` — set phase, outcome, close_price, pools, entries\n\n**Transactions**:\n- `insertTransaction(params)`, `insertTransactions(params[])` — idempotent (ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING)\n- `getTransactions(wallet, cursor?, limit?, game?)` — paginated history, newest first\n- `close()` — gracefully end connection pool\n\n**Data Normalization**:\n- All BIGINT columns (amounts, prices) are normalized to JavaScript `Number`\n- JSONB arrays parsed automatically by postgres.js\n- Date fields converted to ISO strings on insert\n\n---\n\n## 5. Auth DB Module (`auth-db.ts`)\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/auth-db.ts`\n\n**Exports**: `createAuthDb(sql)` → `AuthDb` interface (shares postgres connection pool)\n\n**AuthDb Methods**:\n- `insertChallenge(nonce, wallet, cluster, message, expiresAt)` — create challenge for wallet sign-in\n- `consumeChallenge(nonce)` — atomically set used=TRUE (prevents replay)\n- `insertRefreshToken(wallet, tokenHash, familyId, expiresAt)` — store token for JWT refresh\n- `getRefreshTokenByHash(tokenHash)` — lookup by token hash\n- `revokeRefreshToken(id)` — invalidate single token\n- `revokeTokenFamily(familyId)` — detect token theft (revoke all in family)\n- `cleanupExpired()` — delete stale challenges and revoked tokens\n\n**Auth Tables**:\n- `auth_challenges` — single-use nonces for challenge-response flow\n- `refresh_tokens` — family-based revocation for JWT token rotation\n\n---\n\n## 6. Integration in `index.ts`\n\n**How migrations are invoked**:\n\n```typescript\n// From package.json \"start\" script:\n//   \"start\": \"tsx src/migrate.ts && tsx src/index.ts\"\n\n// Manual in index.ts would be:\nimport { runMigrations } from \"./migrate.js\";\nawait runMigrations(config.databaseUrl);\n```\n\n**Current setup** (index.ts lines 1–30):\n```typescript\nconst sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);       // Wraps postgres connection\nconst authDb = createAuthDb(sql);              // Reuses same connection pool\n\n// db and authDb share the postgres connection\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Schema Summary\n\n**Current Tables** (after all 9 migrations):\n\n| Table | Purpose | Key Columns |\n|-------|---------|------------|\n| `rounds` | Commit-reveal games (Coinflip, Lord) | pda, game, creator, secret, commitment, amount_lamports, match_id, phase (state machine), entries (JSONB), result_hash, winner |\n| `operator_events` | Audit log | pda, event_type, payload (JSONB), created_at |\n| `closecall_rounds` | Pari-mutuel prediction (BTC oracle) | round_id, pda, phase, outcome, green_pool, red_pool, green_entries (JSONB), red_entries (JSONB), close_price, settle_tx |\n| `closecall_candles` | Pyth price history | minute_ts (PK), price, expo, price_human, hermes_vaa |\n| `transactions` | Player transaction ledger | wallet, game, match_id, tx_type (deposit/payout/refund), amount_lamports, tx_sig (unique), created_at |\n| `auth_challenges` | Challenge-response nonces | nonce (PK), wallet, cluster, message, expires_at, used |\n| `refresh_tokens` | JWT token family | id, wallet, token_hash (UNIQUE), family_id, expires_at, revoked |\n| `_migrations` | Version tracking | version (PK), name, applied_at |\n\n**Indexes** (for query optimization):\n- `rounds(phase)`, `rounds(creator)`, `rounds(match_id)`\n- `operator_events(pda, created_at)`, `operator_events(event_type, created_at)`\n- `closecall_rounds(phase)`, `closecall_rounds(settled_at DESC)`\n- `transactions(wallet, created_at DESC)`, `transactions(match_id)`\n- Unique constraints on `transactions(wallet, match_id, tx_type, tx_sig)` (idempotency guard)\n\n---\n\n## 8. Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Numbered file format** (`001_`, `002_`, etc.) — lexicographic ordering ensures correct application sequence\n2. **Transactional safety** — each migration + version record in one transaction prevents partial state\n3. **Idempotent SQL** — `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` allows re-running without errors\n4. **Schema routing** — optional `DB_SCHEMA` env var for multi-tenant setups\n5. **Dev-phase destructive migrations** — `003_tier_to_amount.sql` truncates `rounds` table (acceptable during development, not production)\n6. **State machine enforcement** — phase transitions validated at application layer + recorded via `updated_at` timestamps\n7. **Audit log via operator_events** — immutable append-only record of all state changes (complementary to transaction ledger)\n8. **Idempotent transaction writes** — `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` on `transactions(wallet, match_id, tx_type, tx_sig)` prevents duplicate logging\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/migrations/` — all .sql files\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/migrate.ts` — migration runner\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts` — schema routing\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` — main DB client\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/auth-db.ts` — auth operations\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts` — server bootstrap\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/package.json` — npm scripts (migrate, start)"}],"totalDurationMs":82482,"totalTokens":53397,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":519,"cache_read_input_tokens":49836,"output_tokens":3041,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":519},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
